mbres.it/en/publications/leading-italian-companies |title=Leading Italian Companies |date=October 2014 |publisher=[[Mediobanca]] |access-date=9 February 2015}}</ref> [[Fiat Chrysler Automobiles]], [[CNH Industrial]], [[Ducati]], [[Piaggio]] (motor vehicles); [[Pirelli]] (tyre manufacturing); [[Enel]], [[Edison (company)|Edison]], [[A2A]], [[Terna (Italian company)|Terna]] (energy); [[Eni]] (petrochemicals); [[Candy (company)|Candy]], [[Indesit]], [[De'Longhi]] (home appliances); [[Leonardo S.p.A.|Leonardo]] that has absorbed its subsidiary companies [[Alenia Aermacchi]], [[AgustaWestland]] and [[Oto Melara]] (defence); [[Avio]], [[Telespazio]] (space); [[Beretta]], [[Benelli (firearms)|Benelli]] (firearms); [[Armani]], [[Versace]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Gucci]], [[Benetton Group|Benetton]], [[Diesel (brand)|Diesel]], [[Prada]], [[Luxottica]], [[YOOX]] (fashion); [[Ferrero SpA|Ferrero]], [[Barilla Group|Barilla]], [[Autogrill]], [[Lavazza]], [[Perfetti Van Melle]], [[Davide Campari - Milano|Campari]], [[Parmalat]] (food&beverages); [[Techint]], [[Gruppo Lucchini|Lucchini]], [[Gruppo Riva]], [[Danieli]] (steel); [[Prysmian Group|Prysmian]], [[Salini Impregilo]], [[Italcementi]], [[Buzzi Unicem]], [[Astaldi]] (construction); [[STMicroelectronics]] (electronics); [[Telecom Italia]], [[Mediaset]] (communications); [[Assicurazioni Generali]], [[Unipol]] (insurance); [[UniCredit]], [[Intesa Sanpaolo]] (banking); [[Ferrari]], [[Maserati]], [[Lamborghini]] (luxury vehicles); [[Fincantieri]], [[Ferretti Group|Ferretti]], [[Azimut Yachts|Azimut]] (shipbuilding).\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#d1e4fd;\"\n! Rank (World) !! Rank (Italy) ||  Company !! Headquarters !! Revenue (\u20acbn) !! Profit  (\u20acbn) !! Employees (World) !! Main sector\n|-\n| 19 || 1 || [[Exor (company)|Fiat]] || [[Turin]] || 152.6 || 0.83 || 225,587  || [[Automotive industry|Automotive]]\n|-\n| 49 || 2 || [[Assicurazioni Generali|Generali Group]] || [[Trieste]] || 102.6 || 2.25 || 74,0